how do you enter codes into the gameshark for ps in the several versions of the ps gs i have owned if you press the select button from any screen it will give you a legend that tells you what button does what you should be able to make your way through it it's not complicated once you memorize what all the buttons do by the way a couple of the game sharks i have owned for several different systems over the years didn't come with instructions so this question is not as dumb as some might think if all else fails and you can't figure it out call their tech support number or email your question to support gameshark com GameShark The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time AmigaOS Pump It Up Glitch City Mouse (computing) GoldenEye 007 Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Dance Dance Revolution Konami Code Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Banjo-Kazooie Slot machine Nintendo GameCube Elevator Emacs Gradius Resident Evil (video game) Unicode Beatmania IIDX E-mail DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution 7thMIX Mortal Kombat PlayStation Portable Atari 8-bit family Game Boy Advance Bubble Bobble DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution 6thMIX Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME (North America) Cheat cartridge Microsoft Ecco the Dolphin Xbox 360 PlayStation 2 Game controller Pok__mon (video games) Match Game Nintendo 64 Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Castlevania Legends Tales of Symphonia The Price Is Right WarioWare, Inc.: Mega Party Game$ DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution Nintendo Entertainment System Sega Saturn Sega Dreamcast DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution Tic-Tac-Dough Super Smash Bros. Melee Dance Dance Revolution ULTRAMIX 2 The Chemical Brothers Super Smash Bros. Perfect Dark Nintendo Danger Hiptop Whose Line Is It Anyway? Blue screen of death Dungeons & Dragons: Shadow over Mystara Hello world program Xbox Action Replay Jumpstart 3rd Grade Embedded system IPod Game Boy System Shock Break the Bank Cheat code C64 Direct-to-TV Sonic the Hedgehog (16-bit) Music video game Super Mario Bros. 3 Game show Poker jargon Ope